#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:77 7c84413ee7034905ae3c08475d5b1ac3
msgid "A few conventions worth knowing before writing new tests:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:79 f43df3198a494761b1971c20cc7a583c
msgid ""
"**Default to ``float64`` and ``cpu``** in new tests; add a GPU variant "
"guarded by ``@pytest.mark.skipif(not torch.cuda.is_available())`` when "
"the code path you're exercising has device/dtype handling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:82 5d0f1941e37646419c7d5afb32c489c2
msgid ""
"**Avoid NumPy inside assembler ``forward()`` methods.** Assemblers run "
"under ``torch.vmap``, which is silently incompatible with NumPy arrays — "
"stay in torch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:85 91f0ebf578224fc0943274373ad1065a
msgid ""
"**Name tests after what they exercise**, not the file. Duplicate function"
" names across test files run fine but make ``pytest -k`` filtering noisy."
msgstr ""

