#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:128 983b4c4f2089478a8a1f314bc222520f
msgid "Code style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:130 e759cd8c0d014244955d34958af2a1d2
msgid ""
"There is no automated formatter / linter enforced in CI today, so the "
"working rule is **match the file you're editing**. In practice that "
"means:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:134 f5de217ba0e44698af76628f3b123837
msgid "4-space indent, PEP 8 in spirit, line length around 88-100 characters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:135 2d17f6de3f7049a98291c4b3674ea4d6
msgid ""
"**NumPy-style docstrings** with Summary → Parameters → Returns → Notes → "
"Examples (in that order). Type hints are encouraged but not required; if "
"you add them, prefer ``torch.Tensor`` over the generic ``Any``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:139 4763d1416ebb48419b401e1b45e9cfe0
msgid ""
"Use the existing **``BufferDict`` / ``BufferList``** containers "
"(``tensormesh.nn``) for ``nn.Module``-compatible tensor collections. "
"Don't roll a plain ``dict`` of tensors when crossing ``nn.Module`` "
"boundaries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:143 118d76a1a3054ee3a8a617a862f711e7
msgid ""
"Keep ``forward()`` methods pure tensor code — no Python control flow on "
"tensor values, no NumPy, no ``.item()`` calls unless the result is for a "
"print/log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:149 1579400dee43407e98a5473ddcb88707
msgid "Submitting a pull request"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:151 b6ed2608fb484f94a236a4b19961da0c
msgid "The mechanical flow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:153 8eb726cde81c4d05822e96c556bd054a
msgid ""
"**Fork & branch from ``main``.** Branch naming is informal; "
"``feat/<short>`` / ``fix/<short>`` / ``docs/<short>`` matches the commit-"
"message style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:155 5218763b145347a4bb9b39c47c3c1d6c
msgid ""
"**Write tests.** A PR that touches numerical code without an associated "
"test is unlikely to be merged. CPU + ``float64`` is the minimum; add a "
"GPU variant if the touched code branches on device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:158 fb2dcf21592d4dbf840e1c027d3f9382
msgid "**Run the relevant tests and a docs build** locally; both should be clean."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:160 02bcff9a647e4240b37e754a0d5b6d8e
msgid ""
"**Open the PR**, link the issue with ``Fixes #NN`` (or ``Refs #NN`` for "
"partial fixes), and fill in the body explaining the *why* — not just the "
"*what*, since the diff already covers that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:163 1136486cd0474cd2bd3de4caaf030f8c
msgid ""
"**Commit message style** follows the rest of the project: "
"``<type>(<scope>): <imperative summary>``, e.g. ``fix(ode): propagate "
"u0.dtype/device through step()``. Types in use: ``feat``, ``fix``, "
"``docs``, ``test``, ``refactor``, ``perf``, ``ci``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:169 e71f8e1edef24b63a2b3c0b5539882ae
msgid "What reviewers will look for:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:171 388356a830914164a4c9a8cbbb113bf8
msgid ""
"Tests that exercise the path you changed, including the failure mode "
"before your fix if applicable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:173 b5768b3f74874836bbcc341ea128e685
msgid "No new Sphinx warnings if you touched docstrings or ``.rst``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:174 b1e766fb062e472dbc4b2fc497e853bc
msgid ""
"No accidental backwards-incompatibility — if a public symbol is renamed "
"or removed, the PR description should call it out explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:177 f0356a3b7ef24e689e8e520c2cff7325
msgid ""
"Numerical changes (new element, new quadrature, new solver) should "
"include at least one analytical-reference check."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:180 b82ed299bd0f42f58c210c30e5e5ceee
msgid ""
"This is a small maintainer team; response times are best-effort. If a PR "
"has been silent for more than a week or two, a polite ping on "
":doc:`discord` ``#dev`` is welcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:186 b37abd9616b0498891fa15b613c9142b
msgid "Sign-off and the Developer Certificate of Origin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:188 5615c689cbd944b8a6d18fb25481196f
msgid ""
"Every commit that lands on ``main`` must be signed off under the "
"`Developer Certificate of Origin <https://developercertificate.org/>`_ "
"(DCO) — the same lightweight contribution policy used by the Linux "
"kernel, PyTorch, vLLM, and most Apache-licensed projects. The full text "
"lives in the ``DCO`` file at the repository root; the gist is that you "
"certify the code is yours to contribute (or that it came from a properly-"
"licensed source) and that you are submitting it under the project's "
"Apache 2.0 license."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/contributing.rst:197 2b3b887b52d144b1af0de886c4e6c213
msgid ""
"The mechanics are trivial — pass ``-s`` to ``git commit`` and Git appends"
" the line for you:"
